<div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="mb-5" style="color: #3163bc"><i class="bi bi-question-circle-fill" style="color: #3163bc"></i> Help & Support</h1>
    <div class="row">
        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="faq-box p-4 rounded text-white" style="background-color: #3163bc">
                <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
                <dl>
                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">1. How do I log in to the system?</dt>
                    <dd>Visit the login page and enter your credentials. If you encounter any issues, please contact our Technical Support Team.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">2. How can I reset my password?</dt>
                    <dd>You can reset your password by clicking on the 'Forgot Password' link on the login page. Follow the instructions sent to your registered email address.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">3. What is the Latrobe Scheduling System?</dt>
                    <dd>The Latrobe Scheduling System is a software solution that was designed to manage employee information, subject instance scheduling, and overall scalability for the efficient delivery of Latrobe courses.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">4. Who can access the Latrobe Scheduling System?</dt>
                    <dd>The system is accessible to managers, lecturers, and administrators. Each user type has specific roles and permissions which are tailored to their responsibilities.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">5. Can I access the system from any device?</dt>
                    <dd>Yes, the Latrobe Scheduling System is designed to be accessible from any device with an internet connection.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">6. What should I do if I encounter an error while using the system?</dt>
                    <dd>If you encounter any errors or issues while using the system, please refer to the error messages located in the User Documentation for guidance.</dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">7. How can I provide feedback or report a problem?</dt>
                    <dd>
                        Users can provide feedback or report any problems with the system through the designated support channels listed under the 'Contact Information'.
                        Your feedback is valuable and helps us to improve the system for all its users
                    </dd>
                    <br />

                    <dt class="fw-bold fs-5 mb-2">8. Where can I find additional support and resources?</dt>
                    <dd>Additional help and support resources, including System Maintenance Documentation, Contact Information, and User Manuals, can be found on the Help & Support Page within the system</dd>
                    <br />

                </dl>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Divider -->
        <div class="col-md-1">
            <hr class="d-md-none">
            <hr class="d-none d-md-block" style="border-top: 1px solid #ccc;">
